  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2009-07-22",
    "date": "2009-10-22T14:13:13Z",
    "text": "Notice Pleading Restoration Act of 2009 - Prohibits a federal court from dismissing a complaint for failure to state a claim upon which relief can be granted, or because it is so vague or ambiguous that a party cannot reasonably be required to frame a responsive pleading, except under the standards set forth by the Supreme Court in Conley v. Gibson (thus restoring the system of notice pleading previously used)."
